## -----------------------------------------------------------------------
## RLM Release â€” VM Arguments
## -----------------------------------------------------------------------
## These flags are passed to the Erlang VM when the release starts.
## See: https://www.erlang.org/doc/man/erl.html
## -----------------------------------------------------------------------

## Name and cookie are set by env.sh.eex via RELEASE_NODE / RELEASE_COOKIE.
## Do NOT set -sname/-name or -setcookie here; the release boot script
## handles that automatically.

## Increase the number of concurrent ports/sockets (default: 65536)
## +Q 65536

## Increase the number of simultaneously existing processes (default: 262144)
## +P 262144

## Increase the distribution buffer size for large inter-node messages.
## Default is 1MB; bump to 32MB for sending large trace data across nodes.
+zdbbl 32768

## Set the net tick time (seconds). Nodes that don't respond within
## 4 * net_ticktime are considered down. Default: 60s.
## Lower values detect failures faster but are more sensitive to network jitter.
-kernel net_ticktime 15

## Enable the heart process for automatic restart on VM crash.
## Uncomment for production deployments.
## -heart

## Enable kernel poll (epoll on Linux) for better I/O scaling.
+K true

## Increase async thread pool size (default: 1).
## Useful for file I/O operations in the tool system.
+A 16
